{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29cb3201-dbbd-45ad-935c-4657d5ef622c","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four report the reason in test results so you can track why tests were skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b7776441-42ff-4b91-988a-8804af49672b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":209,"requestId":"0C02:A917E:53D701:622965:69F009B7"},"id":"ec3fd272-d058-4259-b1b6-0d6d679646b8","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:13:32.617Z","parentId":"2b8b7154-23f6-4331-856a-f33fcd193909"}
